# Data Fetching

Use this rule with `.ai/lifecycle/think.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/plan.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/build.md`, and `.ai/lifecycle/test.md`.

Before changing data access, identify the owning API client, cache strategy, loading/error/empty states, and mutation invalidation behavior.

{{#if (eq dataFetching "none")}}
- Centralize HTTP in `src/api/` (or `src/services/`); use typed responses and narrow error shapes.
- Surface **loading / error / empty** states consistently in UI components.
{{/if}}

{{#if hasTanstackQuery}}
- **Query keys** are part of your API: colocate factory functions (`queryKeys.user(id)`).
- Set sensible `staleTime`; invalidate on mutations; prefer `prefetchQuery` for perceived performance.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasSWR}}
- Keys as tuples; align fetcher signatures; use `mutate` for optimistic updates when appropriate.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasApollo}}
- Normalize with cache policies documented per feature; avoid `any` in generated types.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasRtkQuery}}
- Tag types for invalidation; keep endpoints focused; generated hooks only in components that need them.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasTrpc}}
- Use inferred types end-to-end; validate inputs on the server; handle `TRPCClientError` in UI.
{{/if}}

## Pagination

- Prefer **cursor-based** APIs when available; show loading rows or skeletons, not spinners only.

## Auth headers

- Attach tokens in **one** place (interceptor / link / fetch wrapper), not per call site.

## UI State Contract

- Every async view needs loading, error, empty, and success states.
- Mutations should define optimistic behavior, disabled states, retries, and post-success cache updates where relevant.
- Avoid leaking transport errors directly to users; map them to useful UI copy.

## Must Avoid

- Fetching from leaf components when the repo already uses hooks/composables/services.
- Duplicating server-state cache into global client state.
- Inconsistent query keys or mutation invalidation.
- Per-call auth header handling.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Data owner, cache key/invalidation, and UI states are named.
- Error and empty paths are tested or manually checked.
- Auth/session behavior is preserved.
